"geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Resilience erodes&lt;br&gt;nuclear deterrence&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+8+11]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   86k lives-eq/$1k · 58% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up The Humane League · 22%&lt;br&gt;▼ 11 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + resilience_undermines_deterrence&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Peltzman effect for civil defence: making nuclear war survivable weakens deterrence and raises the chance of war, so a resilient-food dollar partly insures against a catastrophe it also makes marginally likelier. An alternative, lower estimate for ALLFED, anchored to Rodriguez&#x27;s ~0.4%/yr US-Russia war probability. Requires future people to be in the circle. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused → 11 resilience_undermines_deterrence" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5_6_8_11.drawio" id="w1_2_5_6_8_11"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1101" y="271" width="287" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Collapse reroll:&lt;br&gt;survivors rebuild wiser&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+8+12]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   86k lives-eq/$1k · 65% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up The Humane League · 23%&lt;br&gt;▼ 11 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + collapse_teaches_better_future&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Collapse-as-reroll, optimistic: survivors of a near-collapse rebuild wiser and more cautious, so much of the value of preventing a survivable collapse is recovered by the better rebuild — resilient-food work aimed at averting collapse is worth less. The opposite of collapse_degrades_future, so the two cannot be held together. Requires the undiscounted far future. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused → 12 collapse_teaches_better_future" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5_6_8_12.drawio" id="w1_2_5_6_8_12"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1027" y="542" width="287" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Collapse reroll:&lt;br&gt;survivors stagnate&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+8+13]&lt;br&gt;→ ALLFED&lt;br&gt;   771k lives-eq/$1k · 73% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up AI safety (Redwood Research) · 18%&lt;br&gt;▼ 11 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + collapse_degrades_future&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Collapse-as-reroll, pessimistic: survivors become durably tech-averse and stagnate, locking in a permanently degraded future close in badness to extinction — so preventing a survivable collapse is worth much more, and resilient foods (ALLFED) can overtake AI safety. The opposite of collapse_teaches_better_future. Requires the undiscounted far future. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused → 13 collapse_degrades_future" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_5_6_8_13.drawio" id="w1_2_5_6_8_13"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="966" y="813" width="366" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Time of perils:&lt;br&gt;space settlement exits it&lt;br&gt;[1+2+5+6+8+14]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;   930k lives-eq/$1k · 51% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up ALLFED · 41%&lt;br&gt;(Toby Ord, Elon Musk)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + time_of_perils_exit&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Time-of-perils optimism: hazard is high during the AI / nuclear transition but collapses once decorrelated, self-sufficient settlements exist — no single catastrophe reaches them all. The window closes, the expected future stretches far past the background-hazard baseline, and x-risk reduction during the window is what unlocks it (Ord, The Precipice; the multiplanetary-backup argument). Mutually exclusive with the view that early expansion re-arms the hazard. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused → 14 time_of_perils_exit" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJy1WGtv2zgW%2FSsXwc6u3XUcyW8nmwXSxpkpJn0gSXcwaAqXlmibG1nUklIcT6fz2%2BeQlGw5UVB3jfkSOBR57rlP3ssvByGfsixKX8mQHxwfHB3R6ekp3SgmYkolBYr9tsKPZUy3WcvzO7SUKgrvBV%2FS0h%2B3xt1xbzwYY72mU5mQ36kbgNsYQGdaZ4skFTKmYA68Y%2FIoYUoGc8EiA%2BcPW%2BTTlKkxW7LVeJ4tWKyLDy1isViwSI%2B1XPDlnKXFly5NszRTPD8wXrA05Wq8F