Jan Narveson, Melinda Roberts)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + space_expansion_backfires + living_in_simulation + person_affecting_view&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Person-affecting population ethics: making happy people is neutral, so the astronomical case for x-risk reduction — which rests on the sheer number of extra future lives saved from extinction — loses almost all its force. Only the harm to people who exist regardless still counts. This is the standard premise longtermism&#x27;s critics deny (discussed as the key objection in Greaves &amp; MacAskill&#x27;s &#x27;The Case for Strong Longtermism&#x27;). It requires no_discounting_future_humans, the astronomical-stakes move it pushes back on. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 6 no_discounting_future_humans → 8 suffering_focused → 15 space_expansion_backfires → 16 living_in_simulation → 17 person_affecting_view" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJzNWWtv20YW%2FSsXxrYrpZJMStbLXi%2FgxHIbrJMatrNBEQfKiByJU1Mc7gxpWU2T394zQ1KiLBpRVl%2F6JVDImXPPfd9Lfz7w%2BZSlYfJK%2Bvzg%2BODwkE5PT%2BlWMRFRIslT7I8lfiwiukvbjntEC6lC%2F0HwBS3ccXvcHffGg7HbHbu9sdunmk5kTG6%2FbmDuIsCdaZ3O40TIiLwAqMfkUMyU9ALBQgPqDtvk0pSpMVuw5ThI5yzSxYs2sUjMWajHWs75ImBJ8aZL0zRJFc8vjOcsSbgaL0QSjH2hPZlGiYhmxfEeRbL8fLxxuzg1IJ1Op1zZA9JLNfdXFLukY%2BbxMX%2BMcQP6jCfMu58KxVfX3R6F4sFcFtFYi3kaMqt48bpPMVcaNxmEeJaGsaS104h5AbG1sYQmRlfLJMDvqQg5wSHr1%2FqQEmMM5vu6QYrDiyICEaksmOJN2JjNOUwiNJ4nAc%2FM%2F08Nu0WexTghT85jqY2ZVgdwN%2FI5EPFIaIumExb5LJQRpznCJGzRp1UUjB4%2BGarmOgwDpXDxgYUpJzm1COuAaVmwl1wnNEmXlBox5qLmZcWO6RZYvxi3cLrkbJby7OLPo7ej67Pb0TlNljTjEVcs4a14WQQm90WyYaEXeNmA25OMhzEikCzWu8jjKjHazqVCGK6MpbOzmSVYHIeC6xbdLOetUM4iqRCKtc9xt0HxsPulbrGso4bOD%2FTq9Yk9OeEJy57GSk7YRIQiAZGJNBr7Jqs%2BOA1yP7bognmJhEymeAaFA7Exf5Q0SEviJiakmsFpow%2BL87PL3w7%2F8ZEmPJQLJIy5a53LH%2FE7X